abstract.text: struct defines a SwiftUI view that provides users with information and next steps after enabling Touch ID on their macOS device. The view includes dynamic content that informs users about the successful activation of Touch ID and guides them on what to do next, such as enabling TouchID as a factor in Okta Verify.

struct defines a SwiftUI view that provides information and actions for users when no suitable biometric authentication (like Touch ID) is detected on their macOS device. The view dynamically updates based on the biometry type and includes interactive buttons for learning more, scheduling reminders, and adding fingerprints.
struct defines an invisible SwiftUI view that dynamically displays different views based on the detected biometry type. It observes changes in the
singleton instance for biometry status changes (such as TouchID enablement and disablement) and updates the view accordingly by swapping
